snippet.title: Every shot from the THREE-HOLE PLAYOFF | THE PLAYERS | 2025
snippet.description:
Check out every shot from the three-hole playoff at THE PLAYERS Championship 2025, where Rory McIlroy outlasted J.J. Spaun to claim his second PLAYERS victory and his 28th win of his PGA TOUR career.

SUBSCRIBE to PGA TOUR now: http://pgat.us/vBxcZSh

The PGA TOUR heads to Ponte Vedra Beach, Florida this week for the THE PLAYERS Championship at TPC Sawgrass. Defending champion and World No. 1 Scottie Scheffler returns to THE PLAYERS Stadium Course at TPC Sawgrass looking to extend his legacy and become the first golfer to three-peat at THE PLAYERS. World No. 2 Rory McIlroy is hoping to recreate some magic at in Ponte Vedra Beach, FL. McIlroy, winner of this year’s AT&T Pebble Beach Pro-Am, captured the THE PLAYERS in 2019, but has had a bit of a mixed bag at TPC Sawgrass since then. With over 75 yards added, THE PLAYERS will be decided over the 7,352 yards that THE PLAYERS Stadium Course at TPC Sawgrass has to offer. Alongside last week's Arnold Palmer Invitational winner Russell Henley, other notable players in the field include Xander Schauffele, Ludvig Åberg, Hideki Matsuyama, Justin Thomas and Rickie Fowler with a total of 48 of the world’s top 50 playing in this year's event. 

Check out https://www.pgatour.com for complete coverage along with all the latest news, scoring, and stats!

snippet.title: 2 STOPPAGE-TIME GOALS ‼️ BIG COMEBACK 😱 Atletico Madrid vs. Barcelona | LALIGA Highlights | ESPN FC
snippet.description:
Check out these highlights as Atletico Madrid defeats Barcelona, 4-2, in LALIGA action. Atletico Madrid jumps out to a 2-0 lead following goals scored by Julian Alvarez and Alexander Sorloth, but goals by Robert Lewandowski and Ferran Torres tie the score. Then Lamine Yamal finds the back of the net in stoppage time to take the lead and Torres tacks on another goal late in the match to complete the comeback for Barcelona.

snippet.title: Surviving the Tornado – March 14 2025 Disaster in the Missouri Ozarks
snippet.description:
Description:
On the night of March 14 2025 at approximately 9:51 PM, a powerful tornado tore through our region in the southern Missouri Ozarks (Oregon County). As we took shelter, weather alerts flooded our phones, warning of the devastation to come. This video documents the raw reality of experiencing such a violent storm firsthand.

We are incredibly fortunate—no lives were lost among our family or animals—but the damage to our land and forest is severe. Sadly, many of our neighbors lost everything. This storm serves as a sobering reminder of nature’s power and the resilience required to rebuild.

If you’re in a position to help those affected by these storms, please consider supporting local relief efforts. We will provide updates as we assess the damage and begin the recovery process.

Thank you for watching, and stay safe out there.

#TornadoSurvival #MissouriOzarks #StormDamage #TornadoOutbreak #storm #stormshelter #damage

snippet.title: Living Off-Grid on a Remote Island – DIY Goat Shelter & Kitchen Reno
snippet.description:
In this episode, we finish up the bushcraft-style goat shelter and then move on to fencing. Instead of clearing a wide-open pasture, we put up fencing around a section of the woods, giving the goats plenty of natural shelter and forage while keeping them safe and contained.

With the warmer weather finally creeping in, we shift focus back to the kitchen. We tear down the interior paneling on one wall, hoping to find old hand-sawn boards underneath. If we do, we’ll leave them exposed and paint them white to give the kitchen a rustic look—like the inside of an old wooden ship. Meanwhile, Kelly guts the pantry under the stairs, getting it ready for new shelving.

While she works inside, I head into the woods, drop a big log, and use bushcraft milling techniques with my chainsaw to cut some hand-milled boards for building out the pantry. As the day winds down, Kelly goes foraging along the beach, collecting sea glass that she turns into wire-wrapped necklaces.

We finish off the video back at the kitchen table, answering some of the biggest questions from the comments in a sit-down Q&A session. We also want your help—we’re figuring out how to give away some of Kelly’s handmade sea glass necklaces in the next video, so drop a comment with your ideas!

Life out here is always changing, always challenging, and always rewarding—thanks for following along!

snippet.title: Chaotic 4x400 caps men's 2025 NCAA indoor championship
snippet.description:
Watch all three sections of the men's 4x400m final — and the lengthy delay/review that followed — at the 2025 NCAA indoor track and field championships. Southern California won the 2025 Division I men's indoor track and field title, clinching the title with the meets final event — the chaotic 4x400 meter relay. Texas A&M got disqualified for flagrantly impeding Arkansas, which campaigned for a re-run of the race but was denied.

After the dust settled, USC outpaced Arkansas to score five points in the 4x4 to give the Trojans the championship win by six points. In total, USC finished with 39 points, while Georgia finished with 33 points in second place. It's USC's first men's indoor title in 53 years.

Subscribe to the NCAA Championship YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/NCAAChampionships?sub_confirmation=1

snippet.title: Kingdom Come Deliverance 2 IS A PERFECTLY BALANCED GAME WITH NO EXPLOITS
snippet.description:
KCD2 Is here and it is rapidly becoming one of the greatest RPGs of all time! Of course as a fan of open world sandbox rpgs like skyrim I am drawn to the adventure that kingdom come deliverance has to offer. Of course similar to your average elder scrolls game the developers have left in some perfectly balanced game design choices that might result in the spiffing brit having to ask an important question. Is Kingdom Come Deliverance 2 A Perfectly balanced game with no exploits? Or perhaps are there bugs, glitches and overpowered features that spiff can use to turn himself into a god. 

What you have seen here today is part of a fantastic perfectly balanced gameplay series on youtube where I go from game to game and break them with wacky exploits to gain things like unlimited gold and infinite money all in a fantastic montage. If you enjoyed this then be sure to check out more. The style is similar to RT game and callmekevin in parts. A large influence on this series has come from Valefisk and The Killian Experience.
